<HEADLINE>
CENTRAL PLAZA INAUGURATED IN SOUTHERN TAIWAN SCIENCE PARK
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Tainan,   Jan.   21  (CNA) 01/21/07  18:54:59 (By Y.L.Kao)
</P>
<P>
The Southern Taiwan Science Park Administration held an
inauguration ceremony Sunday for its newly completed Central
Plaza in connection with celebrations of the park's fourth
anniversary.
</P>
<P>
During the ceremony, Tainan County Magistrate Su Huan-chih, Huang
Kun-hu,  a former National Policy Adviser, and Chen Chun-wei,
director-general of the Southern Taiwan Science Park
Administration, jointly ignited a giant firecracker to mark the
initiation of the new landmark in the park.
</P>
<P>
The Central Plaza can accommodate over 40,000 persons and is
surrounded by the park administration office,  service center,
security office and information technology center.
</P>
<P>
It has an underground parking lot comprised of 416 spaces for
automobiles and 466 for motorcycles.
</P>
<P>
According to Chen, the plaza will serve as a main outdoor
activity center for enterprises in the park, while also
furnishing spaces for parking, shopping, recreation and
restaurants.
</P>
